==English==
===Etymology===
* French ''écacher'' (to crush), itself fr. earlier ''cacher''
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /kæˈʃeɪ/ ''or'' /ˈkæʃeɪ/

===Noun===
'''cachet'''
#a special characteristic or quality.
:# ''I remember when this diner was a popular [[hangout]], but lately it seems to be losing its '''cachet'''.''
#(''arch.'') a [[seal]], as of a letter.
===Synonyms (all sense 1)===
*[[charm]]
*[[je ne sais quoi]]
*[[magic touch]]
*[[oomph]]
*[[zing]]
===Usage (sense 1)===
This word is often used in the negative. e.g., ''to lose/be losing its/oneʼs '''cachet'''''